  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community Violence Reduction and Stabilization of Communities at High Risk</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to contribute to the stabilization and return to normalcy of at-risk communities in the Central African Republic by developing the local economy and strengthening social cohesion. The project is based on three pillars: (1) organization of socio-cultural and sports activities to promote social cohesion (2) rehabilitation / construction of public infrastructures that promote intercommunity exchanges and (3) &#x201C;Labour intensive work&#x201D; (THIMO) coupled with three types of training to encourage the development of the local economy and reduce the vulnerability of populations at risk.</narrative>
  </description>
